    "body": "I use emacs, but unfortunately I don't really use our ipython/emacs integration at all (I used to a very long time ago, but eventually switched to using it in a plain terminal, which I prefer).  So I'm afraid I won't be of much help here.\n\nOur emacs integration has always been brittle and little maintained, sadly. It's very much in need of a good \"champion\" from the community who uses it regularly and can help us stay on top of things.  It's quite hard to test it automatically in CI (I wouldn't know how to), so it tends to break badly and nobody notices for a while until a release happens.\n\nSorry not to offer a better answer. We might just spin that off into a standalone separate little extension that can be maintained by someone else, since evidently we don't have the cycles or expertise to do a good job on this one.\n"
  },
