    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For ipython run in comint mode the best solution is a) use strait ipython b) use it in 'simple' mode which disables all of the prompt toolkit stuff which lets emacs do it's job and handle the typing stuff.\n\nSee the discussion in https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/9399#issuecomment-222003924\n\nI do use IPython + emacs + orgmode every day, but I mostly rely on elpy to make that work (and the issue in #9399 is the first real issue I have had in years).  I will try to keep at least one of my machines on bleeding edge if that will help.\n\nFor the plotting freezing you _must_ (until mpl 2.0) use `%matplotlib` with IPython 5 for the event loop integrations to work.\n"
  },
