    "body": "I I have a very similar issue in emacs on Mac OS X: since the update to IPython 5 I cannot really use matplotlib any more because of this window freezing problem. My solution was also to use ```jupyter console``` but it seems this is also now broken:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nERROR:tornado.application:Exception in callback functools.partial(<function wrap.<locals>.null_wrapper at 0x11411f598>)\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/Users/avigan/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/tornado/ioloop.py\", line 605, in _run_callback\r\n    ret = callback()\r\n  File \"/Users/avigan/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/tornado/stack_context.py\", line 277, in null_wrapper\r\n    return fn(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/Users/avigan/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ipykernel/kernelbase.py\", line 265, in enter_eventloop\r\n    self.eventloop(self)\r\n  File \"/Users/avigan/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ipykernel/eventloops.py\", line 277, in loop_cocoa\r\n    show.mainloop()\r\nAttributeError: 'function' object has no attribute 'mainloop'\r\nJupyter console 5.2.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nSorry I've opened another ticket (#10921) because I have the feeling that there could be a workaround. If I understand correctly, the ```--simple-prompt``` option does not only disable the coloring and complete system but also some things related to events handling. Maybe there could be possibility to disable some of these things separately?\r\n\r\nObviously I don't know much of the inner workings of IPython 5 so it's probably not that simple. Sorry if my proposition seems very naive ;)"
